direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods are part of the standard Java object contract and handle object comparison and hashing in a similar manner.
Both methods involve operations on the internal state of the object (decorated and transformer), though they serve different purposes (comparison vs. hashing).
The hashCode method indirectly depends on the transformer's apply method through the transformer's hashCode, which is used in the calculation.
The hashCode method indirectly depends on the decorated comparator's compare method through the decorated's hashCode, which is used in the calculation.
